#import "template.typ": *

#let metadata = (
  title: "Solo Circuit Consolidation",
  unit: "Group A (3-Axis) | Phase 2 — Stage C5 | E8, E11, E12",
  author: "C.Moroney",
  version: "v1.0.0",
)

#let lesson = (
title: [Solo Circuit Consolidation]

,aim: [
Build solo circuit experience, consolidate all circuit competencies toward C standard, and develop full independence in pre-flight administration.
]

,overview: [
Stage C5 is the solo consolidation phase. Multiple supervised solo circuits are flown, with the instructor conducting periodic dual check circuits to assess progress toward C standard. The student handles all pre-flight administration — NAIPS weather, NOTAMs, and maintenance release review — with the instructor spot-checking rather than leading. This stage continues until the student has accumulated at least 2 hours of solo circuit time and all E8, E11, and E12 competency variables are at or approaching C standard. Short and soft field operations are not part of C5 — they are trained separately as Stage C6.
]

,learning_outcomes: [
#text(size:12pt)[*Knowledge*]
- Explain the factors affecting circuit performance: density altitude, aircraft loading, wind changes
- Describe the flight test standards for all circuit elements (E8, E11, E12)
- Describe the pre-flight administration process: NAIPS weather, NOTAMs, maintenance release review

#text(size:12pt)[*Skills*]
- Fly solo circuits consistently with no instructor input
- Manage all pre-flight administration independently: NAIPS TAF/GAF/GPWT, NOTAMs, maintenance release review and brief
- Apply the stable approach gate every circuit solo
- Apply BUMPFISH on every downwind leg solo
- Fly circuits to progressively tighter tolerances approaching C standard on dual check flights

#text(size:12pt)[*Non-Technical Skills*]
- [SA] Full pilot-in-command awareness with no instructor on board; manage the circuit and traffic independently
- [TEM] Identify and manage threats without instructor prompting; make go-around decisions independently; apply stable approach gate without negotiation
- [HF] Build confidence and automaticity in the circuit environment; recognise and manage personal fatigue; know when to terminate a session
- [CRM] Self-brief before every solo departure; self-debrief after each session; record any deviations honestly
]

,theory_knowledge: [
- Aeroplane Performance — density altitude, circuit performance factors *(Pg 145, 241)*
- Human Factors — fatigue, arousal, decision-making *(Pg 36–40)*
]

,ground_brief_topics: [
Total time: 15 minutes (solo days) / 20 minutes (dual check days) \
Equipment required: Student training record, progress checklist \

*Pre-Solo Self-Brief Template* (every solo session)
- NAIPS: TAF/GAF/GPWT obtained and interpreted; wind, visibility, cloud, validity period; conditions suitable for planned flight duration?
- BOM radar: precipitation checked as supplemental
- NOTAMs: checked; any items relevant to circuit operations today?
- Maintenance release: reviewed; all items acceptable; anything to brief instructor about?
- EFATO plan: where will I land if engine fails today — during takeoff? At 200 ft? At 400 ft? On crosswind?
- Radio failure plan: what will I do if the radio fails while downwind?
- Stable approach gate: I will go-around if any gate criterion is not met at 300 ft — no exceptions
- Personal fitness: IMSAFE complete; am I genuinely fit to fly today?

*C Standard Target Review* (dual check sessions only — 10 minutes)
- Review current standard for each element against C standard criteria
- Identify the 1–2 items closest to C standard and 1–2 items still at S standard; plan the dual check session to target these
- Remind student: C standard means consistent, professional execution with no instructor input or correction
]

,ground_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Instructor*]
- Spot-check student's NAIPS weather interpretation: was the weather read correctly? Are conditions suitable?
- Spot-check NOTAM brief: was anything relevant missed?
- Spot-check maintenance release review: did the student cover all key items?
- Confirm solo weather minima are met before student departs
- Observe all solo circuits from ground with radio available on CTAF

#text(size:12pt)[*Student*]
- Access NAIPS independently; obtain weather; check BOM radar; brief instructor on conditions and suitability
- Check NOTAMs independently; brief instructor on any relevant items
- Review maintenance release independently; brief instructor on all items checked and anything found
- Complete IMSAFE self-assessment and operations whiteboard
- Deliver pre-solo brief to instructor including EFATO plan, radio failure plan, gate commitment, and circuit plan
- Lead pre-flight inspection; complete all documentation independently
]

,in_flight_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Solo Circuits*]
- Student conducts solo circuits; instructor observes from the ground
- Instructor contacts student by radio only if a safety concern is observed
- Student applies stable approach gate every approach; executes go-around without prompting if gate not met
- Student completes BUMPFISH every downwind leg without prompting

#text(size:12pt)[*Dual Check Circuits — conducted at instructor's discretion*]
- Instructor assesses C standard progress against each competency variable
- Assessed elements: circuit shape and height, gate compliance, approach stability, landing accuracy, go-around decision quality, emergency handling, radio calls, BUMPFISH
- Identify progress trajectory; set specific targets for the next solo session
]

,common_errors:[
- *Rushing the touch-and-go reconfiguration solo*: The habit must be consistent without an instructor present — flap and trim before power, every time.
- *Not applying the gate while solo*: If a session debrief reveals the gate was not applied, this is a priority correction before the next solo.
]

,post_flight:[
- *After solo sessions*: Student self-debriefs to instructor; describes each circuit; identifies any deviations and causes; notes gate compliance on every approach
- *After dual check circuits*: Instructor provides assessment against C standard; identify specific targets for remaining solo sessions
- *Pre-flight admin spot-check*: Instructor provides feedback on weather interpretation, NOTAM brief, and maintenance release review quality
- *Progress tracking*: Record solo hours and dual check results; assess trajectory toward Phase 3 readiness
]

,standards_for_progression:[
*Minimum requirements before advancing to Phase 3:*
- ☐ Minimum 2 hours solo circuit time accumulated
- ☐ All E8, E11, E12 competency variables at or approaching C standard on dual check

#text(size:12pt)[*Solo Standard (S) — minimum for solo operations*]
- *Circuit*: Height generally ±100 ft; BUMPFISH complete; all radio calls correct; stable approach gate applied every approach
- *Landing*: Touchdown point +250 m; directional control throughout; go-around at own initiative when gate/abort point not met
- *Emergency handling*: EFATO and EFIC managed correctly; flapless landing competent
- *Pre-flight admin*: All tasks completed independently

#text(size:12pt)[*Certificate Standard (C) — target before Phase 3 entry*]
- *Circuit*: Height ±75 ft; format professional and consistent; BUMPFISH and radio automatic
- *Landing*: Touchdown point +150 m; smooth and consistent hold-off; directional control; gate/abort point applied unconditionally
- *Go-around*: Proactive and timely; no negotiation with the gate criteria
- *Pre-flight admin*: Fully independent; NAIPS TAF/GAF/GPWT interpreted correctly; NOTAMs checked thoroughly; maintenance release reviewed completely and briefed clearly

- *Outcome*: Solo hours recorded in logbook and training record. Dual check results recorded per circuit. Phase 3 commences when minimum requirements are met.
]

,safety:[
- *Weather*: Solo minima apply for all solo sessions per BASIC conditions (or CROSSWIND conditions if crosswind solo authorised); ceiling >1500 ft AGL; visibility >8 km; no significant turbulence
- *Maintenance release*: Student must review maintenance release and brief instructor before every solo flight; any concern = discuss with instructor before flying
- *Emergency Procedures*: EFATO plan must be briefed before every solo flight; radio failure procedure known
- *TEM*:
  - Instructor must be able to observe all solo circuits from the ground; radio available on CTAF throughout
  - If student reports any concern after landing — debrief thoroughly before the next solo
  - If fatigue is detected during self-debrief — end the session; do not continue solo flying
  - Maintenance release review is now a student responsibility — it is a safety-critical habit that must be established here before Phase 3
]

,homework:[
- Read Bob Tait's RAAus Study Guide:
  - Aeroplane Performance: Pg 145, 241 (density altitude, circuit performance)
  - Human Factors: Pg 36–40 (fatigue, arousal, decision-making)
- Before every solo session, complete the pre-solo self-brief mentally or in writing before arriving at the aerodrome:
  - NAIPS weather check; EFATO plan for today's runway; gate commitment; personal fitness
- Reflect after every solo session:
  - "Was the gate applied every approach? Were there any deviations I need to tell the instructor about?"
]
)

#show: body => lesson_plan(metadata, lesson, body)